<title>USA: Fund manager favors growth cyclical shares - report.</title>
<headline>Fund manager favors growth cyclical shares - report.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-02-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Richard Weiss, a fund manager at Strong Common Stock, is favoring technology, media and growth cyclical stocks, saying they are undervalued, Barron's reported.</p>
<p>Weiss is looking for &quot;sound companies with good management selling for 10 or 11 times earnings,&quot; the paper said.</p>
<p>Telxon Corp, Sybase Inc and Data General Corp are among his favorite picks, Barron's said.</p>
<p>Regarding growth cyclicals, Weiss told the paper, &quot;These are good companies, selling for cheap and the worst they do is flat earnings in a lousy economy.&quot;</p>
<p>Weiss's fund recently bought shares of cable maker Belden Inc, pump manufacturer Robbins &amp; Myers Inc and German vacuum-pump maker Pfeiffer Vacuum Technology AG, the paper said.</p>
